Install pip and solve the problem: Python is not recognized as an internal or external command

2024-01-12 by Murad Shaker

Sometimes you suddenly encounter problems with Python on your laptop, and perhaps the matter will arouse your curiosity about the cause of these problems, and you may resort to extensive research and perhaps waste a lot of time to no avail. In this article, you will learn how you can solve an important problem in Python. The problem is: The command prompt is not recognized by Python. It gives an error saying that Python does not exist, even though Python is installed on the computer - and you will also learn in this article how you can install pip, it is very important.

 

If this is a problem that interests you, then this article is for you

As you can see, the command prompt cannot recognize Python even though Python is installed on the computer

First, make sure that you have installed Python on your computer with these simple steps

Now I checked and found that Python is already installed

If you do not have Python, download it through this link: https://www.python.org/downloads/

If you installed Python in this way, you will most likely not see the problems I mentioned,

but in any case, if you see these errors, continue reading this article.

Now follow to this directory:  C:\Users\Name Your Computer\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python312

Now copy the directory and go to Environment variables as shown in the steps:

As you can see, if you follow the above steps, it will work

After the command prompt recognizes Python, we will  install pip  and also make the command prompt recognize pip and find it.

Enter this link : https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py

After entering the link, right-click and click on the “Save as...” option

Now that you have downloaded the file, go to the  folder  in which the file was downloaded and run the command prompt from within the folder containing the file you just downloaded.

As explained here

Type this command in the command prompt: python get-pip.py 

pip is installed on your computer

Now we want to make the command prompt recognize the point, so copy the directory in the command prompt surrounded by white as shown in the image above, and we will return to the environment variables.

Also copy the directory here:  C:\Users\the jhnme\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python312\Scripts 

As you can see, after the steps,  we confirmed and showed that pip is installed and working
